  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 7029.93 sitting between the max negative gamma at 7015 and max positive gamma at 7050, dealers are currently in neutral hedging mode but leaning toward buying pressure as spot approaches the 7015 level where they need to buy delta. The recent -3.6% move over 5 minutes suggests a wall break event, but the PIN regime with massive positive gamma walls above (7050, 7100) should provide strong resistance and stabilizing flows on any bounce attempt. Key levels to watch: 7015 (dealer buying kicks in below) and 7050 (heavy dealer selling pressure above).\n\n**Bottom line:** expect a bounce back toward 7050 with strong resistance there.",
